Royal Wedding - Lady Louise Mountbatten

Lady Louise Mountbatten (1889 - 1965), later Queen Consort of King Gustav VI Adolf of Sweden, pictured on the front cover of the Illustrated London News shortly before her marriage to the widower Crown Prince of Sweden in 1923. Lady Louise was the second daughter of Prince Louis of Battenberg and Princess Victoria of Hesse, and elder sister of Lord Louis Mountbatten. The Crown Prince had previously been married to Princess Margaret of Connaught who had died in 1920 at the age of 38. Date: 1923
